Summaries

five sample summaries

[1] Bregman says poverty is not about bad character or laziness, but simply about not having enough money. Poor people often borrow more, save less, smoke, and eat less healthfully. These behaviors may look irresponsible, but research shows they come from living with scarcity, not from weak character. An American psychologist studied sugarcane farmers in India. They are poor before harvest and richer after. The study showed that before harvest, when money was tight, their IQ scores dropped by about 14 points. Poverty reduced their mental capacity, similar to the effect of losing a night’s sleep. This explains why the poor often make bad decisions: they are forced to focus only on short-term problems. Bregman believes the solution is simple: give people cash. Basic income guarantee can reduce stress, improve health, and allow people to plan for the future. Historical figures like Thomas More, Martin Luther King Jr., and others also supported this idea. Bregman argues that with basic income guarantee, we could finally fight poverty in an effective and human way.
[2] He explained that poverty is not the lack of knowledge with some traits of poor people. An experiment with sugarcorn formers, The town with no poverty, andThe biggest lesson of history. Thatcher said that poverty is a personality defect. He was thinking for a long time about poverty, he noticed the new poverty thinking. An experiment with sugarcorn formers. Research shows that the farmer's IQ is losing 14points because they lack sleep before harvest. Scarcity Mentarity is the fact of poverty. Poor people worry about their daily lives, Time, Money ,and Food. We could buy a new computer to do a good job when our computer was broken. However, poor people could not buy a new computer to do a good job when the computer was broken. It is because they worry about their daily lives so seriously.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
[3] Poor people make poorer decisions than the people who have money, for example drinking and smoking more, or saving and exercising less. At first, it was said that the cause was their character. However, this was partly wrong. All the people will make a poor decision if they were in an environment where the poor are. When people feel they are lacking something, like money, they will make wrong decisions. However, when people have money, their IQ score will rise. They will get smarter, healthy and happy. Children's school performance will improve. Hospitalization rates, domestic violence and mental health complaints will decline. Therefore, it means scarcity mentality is the cause. Poverty changes how people make actions. This is what a researcher discovered in India and Canada. The speaker says, poverty means the lack of money. The rich should stop just giving poor stuff like teddy bears. He claims a basic income guarantee will make an equal and fulfilling society.                                                                                              
[4] Rutger Bregman posted a simple question: why do the poor make so many poor decisions? He was introducing a lot of people. Margaret Thatcher, the famous prime minister of the UK said “Poverty is a personality defect.” George Orwell who is a novelist, essayist, journalist & critic said “Poverty annihilates the future.” There are Thomas More who was a philosopher, Martin Luther King who was a civil rights activist, and Milton Friedman who was an economist, too. The cost of child poverty in the US was $500 billion, but the cost to end poverty in the US was $175 billion. He also said three actions. First, an experiment with sugarcone formers. Poverty is not also a lack of knowledge. Second, the town with no poverty, and he indicated the example of Canada. There, the School performance increased from 1974 to 1978, but the hospitalization rate decreased. Finally, the biggest lesson of history because poverty is not a lack of character and cash.                                                                                                                         
[5] The poor borrow more,save less,smoke more,exercise less,drink more and eat less healthfully. According to the survey of American psychologists in India, The farmers' IQ test scores were much worse on the test before the harvest, the effects of living in poverty corresponds to losing 14 points of IQ. It shows that poverty isn’t a lack of character, It’s a lack of cash. The poor are not making bad decisions because they are dumb,but because they’re living in a context in which anyone would make bad decisions. The speaker suggests that the basic income and he thinks it is the most effective way to reduce poverty. He doesn’t think this way is not old fashioned anymore. Some research shows that when they got basic income, they didn’t quit their job.
